SIMPLE: prostitute
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prostitute
<hw>Pros"ti*tute</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Prostituted</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Prostituting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>prostitutus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>prostituere</ets> to prostitute;
<ets>pro</ets> before, forth + <ets>statuere</ets> to put, place. See
<er>Statute</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To offer, as a woman, to a
lewd use; to give up to lewdness for hire.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Do not
<xex>prostitute</xex> thy daughter.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Lev. xix. 29.
</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To devote to base or unworthy purposes; to give up
to low or indiscriminate use; <as>as, to <ex>prostitute</ex> talents; to
<ex>prostitute</ex> official powers.</as></def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prostitute</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prostitute
<hw>Pros"ti*tute</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>prostitutus</ets>, p.
p.]</ety> <def>Openly given up to lewdness; devoted to base or infamous
purposes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Made bold by want, and <qex>prostitute</qex> for bread.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prostitute</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Prostitute
<hw>Pros"ti*tute</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>prostituta</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A woman giver to
indiscriminate lewdness; a strumpet; a harlot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A base hireling; a mercenary; one who offers himself
to infamous employments for hire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No hireling she, no <qex>prostitute</qex> to praise.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prostitution</ent>⟦br⟧
